Our opportunity: 
We are currently looking for a new addition to our Revenue Accounting Team. This is an exciting position that will report to the Director of Revenue. Youâ€™ll apply your technical knowledge and experience in building out and refining processes for a hyper-growth company. Come and join a leader in the RPA industry and be part of the next phase of our journey! 
You will make an impact by being responsible for: 
Collaborating with Legal, Sales, and Contracts teams to structure deals in order to achieve the best revenue recognition results for the Company 
Guiding the business as they structure new business models and product offerings 
Participating in routine close activities, including invoicing audits, preparation of journal entries, reconciliations and related fluctuation analysis 
Researching and prepare accounting policy memos 
Partnering with cross functional teams to create repeatable and scalable revenue and billing processes 
Participating in implementation of ASC 606 
Providing training to business partners while working closely with them to ensure consistency in application of policies and practices 
Interacting with external auditors as a standard part of your role 
You will be a great fit if you have: 
BS in Accounting or Finance required 
5+ years of similar experience in Revenue Accounting 
CPA or equivalent required 
Big 4 experience a plus 
Excellent understanding and working knowledge of both new and old U.S. GAAP revenue recognition rules 
Familiar with Workday ERP, and SFDC 
Revenue recognition software knowledge 
Highly proficient in excel and good with PowerPoint 
You excel in these key competencies: 
Demonstrates strong interpersonal, written and oral communication skills 
Presents ideas and information in a concise, well organized manner 
Works effectively and collaboratively within and across teams 
Maintains high performance standards; passion for excellence and continuous improvement 
Meets deadlines, prioritizes appropriately and is flexible 
